  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package contains a richly described central claim that appears well-supported by ValidationResults but whose Claim node itself carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom link to any Evidence node — constituting an orphan claim (W-EP-01). ValidationResults carry full provenance chains to Evidence; the Claim does not.",
