      "name": "FDA pump experimental hemolysis measurements — NIH/FDA collaborative study",
      "description": "In-vitro hemolysis measurements collected under ISO 10993-4 protocol for the FDA generic centrifugal pump across the five VAD operating points. Normalized Index of Hemolysis (NIH) converted to HI using standard conversion. N=6 replicates per operating point; inter-laboratory reproducibility confirmed across three independent test sites.",
      "wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4023621"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/mesh-sensitivity-study",
      "type": "Evidence",
      "name": "Three-level mesh refinement study with GCI analysis",
      "description": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted on the FDA pump geometry using coarse (4.2M cells), medium (11.8M cells), and fine (31.5M cells) hexahedral-dominant meshes. Grid Convergence Index computed per Roache methodology; GCI fine < 3.2% for HI predictions at all operating points.",
      "wasDerivedFrom": "https://doi.org/10.1115/1.4028539"
    },
    {
